        <p>طلاب الدراسات العليا في ONMU يأخذون دورات في اللغة الإنجليزية والأوكرانية والروسية وفقا للبرامج والبرامج المعتمدة من قبل وزارة الصحة في أوكرانيا. نأخذ في الاعتبار خصوصيات خدمات الصحة العامة في دولة منشأ المتدربين.</p>
        <p>في&nbsp;  <strong>جامعة أوديسا الوطنية الطبية 'ODNMU' ،</strong> يدرس المواطنون <strong>التاليون&nbsp;</strong> في ذلك الوقت: الولايات المتحدة ، كندا ، المكسيك ، إكوادور ، بيرو ، البرازيل ، تشيلي ، أستراليا ، المملكة المتحدة ، ألمانيا ، إسبانيا ، البرتغال ، فرنسا، النرويج، الدانمرك، السويد، بلغاريا، مولدوفا، روسيا، أوزبكستان، تركمانستان، كازاخستان، طاجكستان، الهند، باكستان، سريلانكا، جزر المالديف، موريشيوس، بنغلاديش، نيبال، إيران، العراق، المغرب، تونس، المملكة العربية السعودية، الإمارات العربية المتحدة الإمارات العربية المتحدة ، البحرين ، اليمن ، إسرائيل ، فلسطين ، الكويت ، عمان ، لبنان ، مصر ، ليبيا ، الجزائر ، ماليزيا ، نيجيريا ، غانا ، بنين ، توغو ، جنوب أفريقيا ، زامبيا ، زيمبابوي ، بوتسوانا ، ناميبيا ، أنغولا ، كينيا ، تنزانيا ، الكاميرون ، أوغندا ، ليسوتو ، الصين ، إلخ.</p>
        <p>دربت جامعة أوديسا الطبية الوطنية أكثر من 600 أستاذ و 1300 طبيب علوم وحوالي 80 ألف طبيب لأكثر من 100 عام ، بما في ذلك أكثر من 10000 مواطن أجنبي وأكثر من 600 دكتوراه في العلوم الأجنبية.</p>" : (($lang == 'en') ? "<p></p><p><strong>The Odessa National Medical University 'ODNMU'</strong>  &nbsp; is the largest medical university in Ukraine and one of the oldest medical universities in Eastern and Western Europe. The medical school opened on 1 <sup>st</sup>  &nbsp;September 1900 in Odessa, in the context of the Great Russian imperial university 'Novorossiysk University. In 1922, the Faculty of Medicine of Novorosisk University in Odessa was reformed and awarded the status of Higher Medical Institution and was renamed 'Medical Institute of Odessa'. After the independence of Ukraine in 1993 Medical Institute of Odessa received the highest 4 <sup>th</sup> &nbsp;Accreditation level and was renamed 'Medical University of Odessa' and in 1997 obtained national status and was renamed 'National University of Odessa Medical'.</p>
        <p><strong>The Odessa National Medical University 'ODNMU'</strong>  &nbsp;was the first among the Ukrainian medical universities to obtain national status in Ukrainian medical universities. It is the most prestigious medical university in Russia, Ukraine and Europe. Scientists from the National Medical University of Odessa have contributed greatly to Ukrainian medicine.</p>
        <p>All our educational programs are regulated and approved by the Ministry of Education and Science of Ukraine and the Ministry of Health of Ukraine. The diplomas awarded to foreign students graduated by the&nbsp;  <strong>National Medical University of Odessa 'ODNMU'</strong>  &nbsp;are legalized by the Ministry of Health of Ukraine and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Ukraine.</p>
        <p><span style='color: #800000;'><strong>The National Medical University of Odessa 'ODNMU' </strong><strong>&nbsp;is recognized by the World Health Organization, IMED, the Indian Medical Council, the Medical and Dental Council of Pakistan, the European Council of Medicine, the General Medical Council (registration limited) of the United Kingdom, etc.</strong></span></p>
        <p><strong><u>The Odessa National Medical University 'ODNMU' </u></strong><u><strong>is recognized by the SADC Board and there is no examination after completing your studies to start working in Southern African countries.</strong></u><u>&nbsp;<strong></strong></u></p>
        <p><strong>The Odessa National Medical University 'ODNMU'</strong>  &nbsp;maintains research and partnership relations with many scientific institutions of the former USSR and around the world, such as the Polish Academy of Medicine, the University of <strong>Odessa</strong> Cambridge, Virden University, urgent medicine clinics in Germany and Belgium, Austria and Israel. Cardiff Medical Center (England), Sent-Etien Medical Center (France), New York Medical Center, Ukrainian Medical Society in Canada and Austria.</p>
        <p>In recent years, our workers have had the opportunity to work abroad as specialists and teachers in universities in the United States, Yemen, Germany, the United Kingdom, etc.&nbsp; <strong>The Odessa National Medical University 'ODNMU'</strong>  &nbsp;is proud of the fact that its workers were scientists whose contribution to the world medical science was commonly recognized.</p>
        <p>The National Medical University of Odessa started training English language students in 1993. It was the first medical university in Ukraine, Russia and Eastern Europe to begin training in English. Subsequently, many other medical colleges also opened medical schools in English.</p>
        <p>The faculty of the National Medical University of Odessa is composed of more than 1000 doctors. <strong>It is the largest number of academics working at the Medical University of Ukraine and all over Europe.</strong></p>
        <p>The National Medical University of Odessa has 8 faculties, a faculty of medicine and a department of preparation for foreign students. 58 theoretical departments and 45 clinical departments work at the National Medical University of Odessa. Except for them, the ODNUM has a university multiple clinic and ODNMU dental clinic. Today, more than 9,000 students are trained at the National Medical University of Odessa, including 1,900 foreign students from 52 countries.</p>
        <p>In recent years, ODNMU has created unique scientific and medical research departments, which include ODNMU Dental Clinic, ODNMU Multidisciplinary University Clinic, Molecular Genetics and Cellular Medicine Research Institute, Clinical Research Institute for Biophysics . With the help of the Ministry of Health of Ukraine at the National Medical University of Odessa, the following diagnostic centers have been opened: cardiology, hematology, microsurgery of the eye, synthesis, endoscopy and laser surgery, pediatric cardiology , toxicology and others.</p>
        <p>The ODNMU has a well-established library with computer rooms and an electronic library with 1140 seats. Students receive a ticket for junior and senior years and can use library books at any time.</p>
        <p>The National Medical University of Odessa (ONMU) offers a wide range of undergraduate courses including general medicine, pediatrics, dentistry, pharmacy, nursing and foreign student preparation department, as well as postgraduate course including clinical residency and doctoral programs.</p>
        <p><span style='color: #800000;'><strong>The faculties are as follows:</strong></span></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>GENERAL MEDICINE (MD / MBBS)</strong><br>  
                Course duration: 6 years&nbsp;  <br>
                Degree awarded: Doctorate in Medicine (MD or MBBS).</li>
                <li><strong>PEDIATRICS&nbsp; </strong><br>  
